HOUSE JOINT RESOLUTION 639
By Boyd
A RESOLUTION to honor Master Sergeant Nicole Hanson,
Lebanon High School Air Force Junior ROTC
aerospace science instructor.
WHEREAS, Master Sergeant Nicole Hanson honorably served in the United States Air
Force for twenty-two years; and
WHEREAS, Master Sergeant Nicole Hanson completed an instructor internship at
Springfield High School's Air Force Junior ROTC program; and
WHEREAS, Master Sergeant Nicole Hanson became the Lebanon High School Air
Force Junior ROTC program's aerospace science instructor; and
WHEREAS, she began working diligently as the program had been in need of a second
instructor; and
WHEREAS, during her first year as an instructor, Master Sergeant Hanson was awarded
the Air Force Junior ROTC Outstanding Instructor Award; and
WHEREAS, Master Sergeant Hanson served as the program's only instructor during the
summer of 2024 through February 2025; and
WHEREAS, Master Sergeant Nicole Hanson was offered a job that was closer to home;
however, she chose to remain in her current position and continue her service, even though her
commute to Lebanon is lengthy; and
WHEREAS, to keep the Junior ROTC program afloat and successful, she has made
personal sacrifices; and
WHEREAS, Master Sergeant Hanson has been a great mentor and leader to the
Lebanon High School Air Force Junior ROTC program; and
